'''Lala de Cizique''' ({{lang-el|Λάλα}}) was a Greek woman from [[Cyzicus]] who may be the first [[illuminated manuscript|manuscript illuminator]] known by name. She "painted on ivory and on parchment in Rome during the first Christian century".<ref>{{cite book|last=Addison|first=Julia de Wolf Gibbs|author-link1=Julia de Wolf Gibbs|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rgVBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA341|title=Arts and Crafts in the Middle Ages: A description of Mediaeval workmanship in several of the departments of applied art, together with some account of special artisans in the Early Renaissance|year=1921|publisher=L. C. Page & Company|pages=341–342|accessdate=17 August 2012}}</ref>
