Short-lived titles include ''Codename: Ninja''{{Citation needed|date=January 2018}} and ''Zombee''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.comics.ign.com/articles/741/741394p1.html |title=Zombee Review&nbsp;– Comics Review at IGN |publisher=Uk.comics.ign.com |date=2006-10-24 |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> The ''[[Amelia Rules!]]'' series included ''A Very Ninja Christmas''.
Ninja have supporting roles in ''[[Karate Kommandos]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.misterkitty.org/extras/stupidcovers/stupidcomics102.html |title=Stupid Comics |publisher=Misterkitty.org |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> ''[[Lucha Libre (comics)|Lucha Libre]]'' ''[[Les Naufragés d'Ythaq]]'',{{cn|date=September 2018}} ''[[Masters of the Universe]]'' (Ninjor),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.he-man.org/collecting/toy.php?id=1241 |title=Ninjor |publisher=He-Man.org |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> ''[[Rebirth (manhwa)|Rebirth]]'' (the hero's ally, Eiji Inaba),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animevice.com/eiji-inaba/18-29679/ |title=Eiji Inaba (anime/manga character) |publisher=Animevice.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926073853/http://www.animevice.com/eiji-inaba/18-29679/ |archivedate=September 26, 2013 }}</ref> ''[[Sam Noir]]'' (villains),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thrillingdetective.com/eyes/sam_noir.html#special |title=Sam Noir |publisher=Thrillingdetective.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> ''[[Scott Pilgrim]]'' (Roxanne "Roxie" Richter), ''[[Spike: Shadow Puppets]]'', ''[[Sonic the Hedgehog (comic book)|Sonic the Hedgehog]]'' (Uma Arachnis and the Arachne), ''[[The Order of the Stick]]'' (Therkla and others), ''[[The Tick]]'' (Oedipus),<ref>{{cite web|author=Michael R. Legg |url=http://www.thetick.ws/comheroes.html |title=The Tick comics gallery of superheroes |publisher=Thetick.ws |date=1998-09-27 |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> and ''[[Usagi Yojimbo]]'' (ninja of the Neko,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usagiyojimbo.com/other/characters/neko-ninja.html |title=Neko Ninja&nbsp;– Usagi Yojimbo Dojo |publisher=Usagiyojimbo.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> Mogura and Komori clans, including Kashira Chizu).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usagiyojimbo.com/characters/chizu.html |title=Usagi Yojimbo Dojo&nbsp;– Kashira Chizu |publisher=Usagiyojimbo.com |date=2004-01-13 |accessdate=20