==={{anchor|In tourism and other business|Tourism and other business}}Business=== [[File:Igatetsu-865F.JPG|thumb|alt=Subway train with cartoon characters and lettering on its side|[[Iga Railway Line]] ninja-themed trains in [[Mie Prefecture]], Japan in 2010]] [[File:Become a Ninjutsu expert at the Ninja’s hometown – Koka Ninja Village.jpg|thumb|alt=Four young women dressed in black|Attendees of a 2011 one-day ninja camp in Koga Ninja Village, [[Kōka, Shiga]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.biwako-visitors.jp/reports/ninja/ |title=Become a Ninjutsu expert at the Ninja’s hometown&nbsp;– Koka Ninja Village : Travel Guide of Shiga Prefecture - go.biwako |publisher=En.biwako-visitors.jp |date=2010-11-28 |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref>]] [[Iga Ueno Ninja Festa]], the annual ninja festival in [[Iga, Mie|Iga]] in the former [[Iga Province|province of Iga]], has had ninja-inspired performances, competitions and opportunities to practice ninja skills since 1964.<ref>{{cite news|author=Kim Kyung Hoon |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/worldNews/idUKT11889720080408?feedType=RSS&feedName=worldNews |title=Japan village exposes secret world of ninja fighters &#124; World &#124; Reuters |publisher=Reuters |date= 2008-04-08|accessdate=2010-06-30}}</ref> Iga also has the [[Iga-ryu Ninja Museum]], ninja-style restaurants and cafes.<ref name="guardian"/> In the United States, ninja-themed restaurants include Ninja New York in New York City<ref>{{cite web|author=Hiro Odaira|url=http://www.ninjanewyork.com/ |title=NINJA NEW YORK Restaurant, Finest Japanese Cuisine |publisher=Ninjanewyork.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> and the Flying Ninja sushi bar in San Francisco.{{Citation needed|date=January 2018}} There are American roller coasters named Ninja, such as [[Ninja (Six Flags Magic Mountain)|Ninja]] in California and [[Ninja (Six Flags St. Louis)|The Ninja]] in Missouri.
Other ninja attractions in Japan<ref name=guardian/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gojapan.about.com/cs/chuburegion4/a/ninja.htm |title=Guide to Japanese Ninja attractions&nbsp;– Japan Travel Guide |publisher=Gojapan.about.com |date=2013-07-25 |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web-japan.org/kidsweb/travel/ninja/index.html |title=Touring Famous Ninja Villages&nbsp;– Travel&nbsp;– Kids |publisher=Web Japan |date= |accessdate=2013-08-04}}</ref> include the Koga Ninja Village<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koka.ninpou.jp/index.html |title=甲賀の里 忍術村 |publisher=Koka.ninpou.jp |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> and Kogaryu Ninjutsu Yashiki (Ninja Houses)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kouka-ninjya.com/ |title=甲賀流忍術屋敷 公式ホームページ |publisher=Kouka-ninjya.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> in Koga-gun, [[Shiga Prefecture]], the Togakushi Ninja Village for children,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninjamura.com/ |title=チビッ子忍者村ｰ信州戸隠 そばと忍者の里 &#124; 信州戸隠・子供から大人まで楽しめる忍者アミューズメントパーク |publisher=Ninjamura.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> the Togakushi Ninpo Museum and Karakuri Yashiki (Ninja House)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flame.jp/minzokukan/minzokukan_1.html |title=戸隠民俗館・からくり屋敷・忍法 |publisher=Flame.jp |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> in [[Togakushi, Nagano]], the [[Edo Wonderland Nikko Edomura|Edo Wonderland]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edowonderland.net |title=Edo Wonderland 日光江戸村 |publisher=Edowonderland.net |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> theme park in [[Nikkō, Tochigi]] and the restaurants Men no Sato<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/female-ninja-serve-up-noodles-amidst-silly-complaints-1479428147|title=Female Ninja Serve Up Noodles Amidst Silly Complaints|author=Brian Ashcraft|publisher=Gawker Media|work=Kotaku|accessdate=15 December 2014}}</ref> and Ninja Akasaka in Tokyo<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninjaakasaka.com/ |title=Ninja Akasaka |publisher=Ninja Akasaka |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> and Ninja Kyoto in [[Kyoto]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninja-kyoto.co.jp/ |title=NINJA KYOTO Restaurant＆Labyrinth｜忍者京都迷宮殿 |publisher=Ninja-kyoto.co.jp |date=2009-11-14 |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://karasuma.keizai.biz/headline/1690/ |title=「NINJA KYOTO」にビアホール－「くノ一」が踊るメニューも - 烏丸経済新聞 |publisher=Karasuma.keizai.biz |date= |accessdate=2015-11-06}}</ref>
Businesses include Ninja Jump, an American company producing licensed inflatables;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninjajump.com/ |title=home of licensed bounce houses, waterslides, jumpers and games |publisher=Ninja Jump |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Web Ninja, an Australian e-commerce website-design team;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.webninja.com.au/ |title=Ecommerce Accounting Software Integrated into Website Design |publisher=Web Ninja |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Ninja Message, an Australian direct-to-voicemail service;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ninjamessage.com.au |title=&#124; Home |publisher=Ninjamessage.com.au |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Ninja Tracking Systems, a British GPS developer;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninjatracking.co.uk/ |title=Ninja Tracking Systems &#124; GPS Tracking &#124; GPS Tracker |publisher=Ninjatracking.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Ninja Polish, an online nail-polish retailer;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ninjapolish.com/home.php |title=Ninja Polish |publisher=Ninja Polish |date=2013-09-18 |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Ninja Pyrate, a fire-show-equipment workshop;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ninjapyrate.com/ |title=NinjaPyrate.com |publisher=NinjaPyrate.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131106145309/http://ninjapyrate.com/ |archivedate=November 6, 2013 }}</ref> Crystal Ninja, a crystal design studio;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://crystalninja.com/ |title=Custom, MADE WITH SWAROVSKI速 ELEMENTS Cell Phone Bling & Clothing Accessories |publisher=Crystal Ninja |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> Lactose Ninja, a manufacturer of lactose-intolerance remedies<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lactoseninja.com/ |title=>> Taking the Scary Out of Dairy! |publisher=Lactose Ninja |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> and the Ninja Company, a Eurasian toy manufacturer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theninjacorporation.com |title=Tube Town toys and Pop-up toys from |publisher=The Ninja Corporation |date= |accessdate=2013-11-03}}</ref> {{clear}}
===1998 East Java ninja scare=== {{Main|1998 East Java ninja scare}}
The [[1998 East Java ninja scare]] was an outbreak of [[mass hysteria]] in [[East Java]], [[Indonesia]], in which the local population believed they were being targeted by sorcerers known as [[ninja]], who were blamed for mysterious killings of religious leaders by assassins dressed in black. As many as 150-300 “sorcerers” were killed between February and October, with the most deaths occurring between August and September.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kristof |first1=Nicholas D. |title=Fears of Sorcerers Spur Killings in Java |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1998/10/20/world/fears-of-sorcerers-spur-killings-in-java.html |accessdate=June 6, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=October 20, 1998}}</ref>
