{{Infobox award | name = Rechter Prize | image = | description = Israeli architecture | presenter = | country = [[Israel]] | year = 1962 | website = }} The '''Rechter Prize''' is an Israeli architecture prize awarded bi-annually and intended to "encourage landmark projects of Israeli architecture".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aiq.co.il/pages/EnglishArticle.asp?id=185 |title=AIQ-Architecture of Israel-Editor Ami Ran |publisher=Aiq.co.il |date= |accessdate=2010-04-20}}</ref> It was established in 1962 and name in honour of [[Zeev Rechter|Ze'ev Rechter]].
